    "description": "I just noticed that ProjectionPlot and OffAxisSlicePlot are broken in the current tip, so I'm issuing this pull request to fix it.\r\n\r\nThis also includes a number of fixes to docstrings and renames the slice and projection plots associated with plot collection.  It might be a good idea to figure out how to get plot collection to carry around collections of new style SlicePlots and ProjectionPlots.\r\n\r\nUpdate: Fixing the way callback arguments are handled.  This takes care not to pass self in a wrapper function.  This resolves issue 398.\r\n\r\nUpdate 2: This fixes user-defined callbacks defined in my_plugins.py.  This came up during testing for the PR.\r\n\r\nUpdate 3: This updates the set_width function to accept (width,unit) pairs.  Nonsquare windows are supported by supplying a tuple for the width.\r\n\r\nUpdate 4: Adding docstrings for set_cmap() and save()\r\n\r\nUpdate 5: Removing stray pdb calls.\r\n\r\nUpdate 6: Fixing set_cmap.\r\n\r\nUpdate 7:  Several fixes including avoiding a yt.mods import, fixing support for non-square windows, adding some docstrings, and making it so that set_center can be supplied with units.\r\n\r\nUpdate 8: @Xarthisius noticed some mistakes in the off axis slice class.  This fixes it.\r\n\r\nUpdate 9: non-iterable widths were broken, this fixes it.\r\n\r\nUpdate 10: Resolving the conflict by merging with the tip of the dev branch.  Fixing a but in set_width similar to the ones fixed in 78281ab38f47\r\n\r\nUpdate 11: Fixing another issue that caused width-tuples to break.\r\n\r\nUpdate 12: OffAxisSlicePlot was hopelessly broken.  This fixes it.\r\n\r\nUpdate 13: In response to http://lists.spacepope.org/pipermail/yt-users-spacepope.org/2012-July/002783.html we've decided to center the plot on the center of the domain by default.  The maximum density cell can be selected by choosing center='m' or 'max'.  The plots in the plots dict now have a cb attribute that points to the colorbar object.  This allows the user to directly manipulate the colorbar.  Several other minor style fixes.\r\n\r\nUpdate 14: Fixing a set_zlim so that it doesn't affect plots for all fields.  Thanks @swskillman!",
